The solid state method was employed in synthesis of a series of Ca
analytic grade purity and purchased by Aladdin Industrial Corporation. Typically, as synthesis of
mixing raw materials with stoichiometric ratio and then grinding for nearly 10 min at agate mortar. Next the
mixture was placed into an alumina crucible and pre-sintered at 1000 °C for 1 h and annealed at 1500 °C for 4 h.
Finally, as-synthesized samples naturally cooled to room temperature and ground into powder for measurement.
The XRD patterns of all as-synthesized samples were measured by
X-ray powder diffractometer (D8 Advance, Bruker Corporation, Germany) with Cu-K
under the condition of 40 KV and 30 mA, and the range from 10° to 80°. The SEM images were identified by
high resolution field emission scanning electron microscope (JSM-7001F). The FT-IR patterns were identified on
Fourier transform infrared spectrometer (Spectrum 100, Perkinelmer). The PL and PLE spectra at room temper-
ature were recorded by fluorescence spectrometer (Hitachi F-4600) with a excitation resource xenon lamp (400 V,
150 W), and a 400 nm cut-off filter was used. The decay curves were measured by a spectro-fluorometer (Horiba,
Jobin-Yvon TBXPS). Above of measurements are under room temperature. The temperature-dependence spectra
were recorded on a spectro-fluorometer (Horiba, Jobin-Yvon Fluorolog-3 FL3-21), combined with a self-made
heating attachment and a computer-controlled electric furnace (Tianjin Orient KOJI Co. Ltd, TAP-02).
